      <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;During Hilbert&amp;rsquo;s life, Leibniz&amp;rsquo;s Dream [&amp;ndash; all truths of the reason would be reduced to a kind of calculation directed by symbols &amp;ndash;] by and large, just stayed a dream. [&amp;hellip;] In the 2nd half of the 20th century, things shifted with the advent of computers, as more and more people began to adopt formal techniques. Parts of Leibniz&amp;rsquo;s Dream became reality [&amp;hellip;].&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ndash; &lt;cite&gt;Edsger W. Dijkstra (1930-2002), Under the Spell of Leibniz&amp;rsquo;s Dream.&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
